egies directly from task-specific objectives like entity recognition F1-score. By preserving cell-level integrity while enhancing internal semantic coherence, LISA enables more accurate identification of multi-word entities, improves robustness to OCR noise, and reduces over-segmentation errors. This approach has broad implications for financial reports, medical records, and legal contracts, where precise interpretation of intra-cell content is essential. Moreover, unlike prior work focusing on global structure (e.g., hypergraphs or concept hierarchies), LISA targets an overlooked micro-level problem with macro-level impact.",
